DTSTAMP:20260614T124021Z
DTSTART:20251203T020000Z
DTEND:20251203T025500Z
SUMMARY:Otagi Nenbutsuji (1200 stone faces)
DESCRIPTION:~30 min walk uphill from bamboo grove. 1200+ rakan stone figures carved by amateur sculptors 1981–91 — each face is a different emotion: smiling\, drinking\, meditating\, laughing\, crying. Quiet\, atmospheric\, very photogenic.\n~300 JPY pp\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Otagi%20Nenbutsuji%20(1200%20stone%20faces)%2C%2035.0341%2C135.6646
LOCATION:2-5 Sagatoriimoto Fukatanicho\, Ukyo Ward\, Kyoto
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Otagi%20Nenbutsuji%20(1200%20stone%20faces)%2C%2035.0341%2C135.6646
GEO:35.0341;135.6646
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:japan-honeymoon-2025-d10-2b@trip-atlas
DTSTAMP:20260614T124021Z
DTSTART:20251203T030000Z
DTEND:20251203T035500Z
SUMMARY:Adashino Nenbutsuji (8\,000 Buddhas)
DESCRIPTION:5 min walk back down from Otagi. Thousands of small weathered stone Buddhas memorializing the forgotten dead\, plus a small bamboo grove behind the main hall. Less famous than the main Arashiyama grove — but you'll have it almost to yourselves.\n~500 JPY pp\nhttps://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Adashino%20Nenbutsuji%20(8%2C000%20Buddhas)%2C%2035.0282%2C135.6682
LOCATION:17 Sagatoriimoto Adashinocho\, Ukyo Ward\, Kyoto
URL:https://www.google.com/maps/search/?api=1&query=Adashino%20Nenbutsuji%20(8%2C000%20Buddhas)%2C%2035.0282%2C135.6682
GEO:35.0282;135.6682
END:VEVENT
